## Idea

For $(-)^n \colon \mathbb{G}_m \longrightarrow \mathbb{G}_m$ the [[endomorphism]] of powering by $n$ on the [[multiplicative group]] over an [[Ã©tale site]], then if $n$ is invertible over the site then there is a [[short exact sequence]]

$$
  0 \to \mu_n \to \mathbb{G}_m \stackrel{(-)^n}{\to} \mathbb{G}_m \to 0
  \,,
$$

where $\mu_n$ is the [[group of units]] of order $n$.

This is called the _Kummer sequence_.

